<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Cleaning,
        Inspection, and Testing - Cylinder Head Inspection - Valves Installed
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.3.2" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="8">
        <title>Cylinder Head Inspection - Valves Installed</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para id="s10.3.2.ref1">Inspect cylinder head for thickness, warping, cracks, and valve leakage.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450010047" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08163.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measurement of cylinder head thickness</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To determine if cylinder head has been resurfaced previously, use a 3-4 inch micrometer to
                measure deck thickness of cylinder head at four corner locations. If overall cylinder head thickness
                (deck-to-deck)
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">specification</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t1"/>
                is not met, install new cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010048" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08158.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Check for gasket surface flatness</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a straightedge and feeler gauge to check gasket surface of cylinder head for flatness.
                Check for flatness horizontally, diagonally, and transversely. If
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t1"/>
                are not met, install new cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010049" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08157.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking valve head recession</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve head</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before removing valves, check valve head recession (relative to deck) as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a straightedge across each valve.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a feeler gauge between straightedge and valve head.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If out of
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s10.t1"/>, replace valve. Repeat step 2 with new valve, and if specifications are still
                    not met, replace cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Dye Penetrant Kit PT-7191</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>, to inspect for cracks in cylinder head
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010050" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0832.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Cleaner sprayed on cylinder head (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spray cleaner on lower deck (gasket surface) of cylinder head and wipe dry.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010051" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0833.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Dye penetrant sprayed on cylinder head (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spray dye penetrant on lower deck (gasket surface) of cylinder head and let dry for 5 to 15
                minutes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wipe dye off cylinder head surface.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dye will remain in cracks.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010052" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0888.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Spraying developer onto cylinder head (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f3450010053" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0835.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder head crack between intake and exhaust valves (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spray developer on lower deck (gasket surface) of cylinder head and let dry for 5 to 15
                minutes. Cracks show up as purple lines against white developer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install a new cylinder head if cylinder head is cracked.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position cylinder head on wooden blocks with gasket surface facing down and spray mineral
                spirits into intake and exhaust ports.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010054" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08166.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Leak inspection</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inspection mirror</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Reflection of valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flashlight</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wait five minutes. Use an inspection mirror to inspect valve seat area for leakage of
                mineral spirits.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Valve seats must not leak. Valve replacement is not required if the cylinder head passes the
                    mineral spirits test. If valve seats leak, install new valves. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_211.xml" xrefid="s10.2.8.ref1">Valves</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s10.2.8.ref1"/>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
